  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::MedicineInteract
  shelfName: Skin_Hair_And_Creams
  medicineNames:
  - La Roche-Posay Cicaplast
  - Bioderma Sebium Gel
  - Eucerin Urea Repair
  - Ducray Anaphase Shampoo
  - Cerave Moisturizing Cream
  - The Ordinary Niacinamide
  - Sebamed Clear Face Gel
  - Mustela Stretch Marks Cream
  - Phyto Hair Serum
  - Avene Cleanance Cream
  descriptions:
  - Repairs damaged and irritated skin
  - Deep cleansing gel for oily skin
  - Moisturizing cream for dry skin
  - Strengthens weak and falling hair
  - Hydrates face and body skin
  - Helps reduce acne marks and oiliness
  - Soothes acne-prone skin
  - Used for stretch mark prevention
  - Hair strengthening serum
  - Cream for acne and sensitive skin
  dosages:
  - Apply twice daily
  - Use morning and evening
  - Apply after shower
  - Use shampoo three times weekly
  - Apply daily on dry areas
  - Use 3 drops at night
  - Apply after washing face
  - Apply twice daily during pregnancy
  - Use on scalp once daily
  - Apply thin layer before sleep
  warnings:
  - Avoid contact with eyes
  - For external use only
  - Stop use if irritation occurs
  - Do not overuse product
  - Keep away from children
  - Use sunscreen during treatment
  - Avoid applying on wounds
  - Store in cool place
  - Consult doctor for severe reactions
  - Do not mix with strong acids
