  - Mucosolvan Syrup
  - Panadol Cold & Flu
  - Otrivin Nasal Spray
  - Fluimucil Sachets
  - Zyrtec Syrup
  - Ventolin Inhaler
  - Strepsils Lozenges
  - Actifed Syrup
  descriptions:
  - Relieves cough and throat irritation
  - Used for dry cough relief
  - Helps remove mucus from chest
  - Treats cold and flu symptoms
  - 'Relieves blocked nose '
  - Thins mucus in the lungs
  - Treats allergy symptoms
  - Helps open airways for breathing
  - Soothes sore throat
  - Relieves cough and nasal congestion
  dosages:
  - 10 ml three times daily
  - 5 ml every 8 hours
  - 5 ml twice daily
  - One tablet every 6 hours
  - One spray every 8 hours
  - One sachet daily
  - 5 ml once daily
  - 2 puffs when needed
  - One lozenge every 4 hours
  - 5 ml every 8 hours
  warnings:
  - Do not exceed daily dose
  - Avoid use for children under 2 years
  - Drink plenty of water
  - May cause drowsiness
  - Do not overuse nasal spray
  - Use under medical advice
  - Avoid driving after use
  - Keep inhaler clean
  - Do not swallow whole
  - Not suitable with high blood pressure
